<paragraph id="F57B36DAFFF2AF6FFF0B9188FBD9FDDA" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFF0B9188FEC1FDA2" bold="true" box="[199,337,511,536]" pageId="9">Description</emphasis>
. Adult specimens exhibit whitish–orange body coloration when observed in reflected light. The body is 
<quantity id="323C9B3FFFF2AF6FFF399253FEEEFD86" box="[245,382,548,572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.7 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="323C9B3FFFF2AF6FFE399253FDEFFD86" box="[501,639,548,572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.2 mm</quantity>
wide. The anterior region is rounded in shape, whereas the posterior region is spatula–shaped when the specimen is attached to the substrate (
<figureCitation id="6DFF2A5FFFF2AF6FFC099230FBADFDDA" box="[965,1085,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1242,1264]" captionTargetBox="[430,1155,193,1221]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[430,1156,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Macrostomum tuba Graff,1882.A, Dorsalview of a mature specimen;B, Posterior body region withdetails of the copulatory organs; C, Detail of the penis stylet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1084066/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figure 5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F57B36DAFFF2AF6FFF0B921BFD78FC1F" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="9">
Male reproductive system: Two ellipsoid–shaped testes at the sides of the body, approximately at the beginning of the intestine. A thin-walled false seminal vesicle stores sperm and continues into a thick-walled, muscular seminal vesicle through a thin and short intervesicular duct. The seminal vesicle is about a quarter of the size of the false seminal vesicle. Distally, the seminal vesicle connects to the prostate vesicle. Within the prostate vesicle, granulations are observed. These are grouped in small and long sacs that enter the stylet proximally (
<figureCitation id="6DFF2A5FFFF2AF6FFAD4928BFA1FFCAF" box="[1304,1423,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1242,1264]" captionTargetBox="[430,1155,193,1221]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[430,1156,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Macrostomum tuba Graff,1882.A, Dorsalview of a mature specimen;B, Posterior body region withdetails of the copulatory organs; C, Detail of the penis stylet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1084066/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figure 5B</figureCitation>
). The stylet is a slightly-curved, long and slender tube (
<figureCitation id="6DFF2A5FFFF2AF6FFD389368FCFBFC82" box="[756,875,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1242,1264]" captionTargetBox="[430,1155,193,1221]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[430,1156,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Macrostomum tuba Graff,1882.A, Dorsalview of a mature specimen;B, Posterior body region withdetails of the copulatory organs; C, Detail of the penis stylet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1084066/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figure 5C</figureCitation>
). The stylet is 206.9 µm long (162.5–291.5 µm; 
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFA429356FA0CFC82" box="[1422,1436,801,824]" italics="true" pageId="9">n</emphasis>
= 8; 
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFF069333FF73FCE7" box="[202,227,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="9">sd</emphasis>
= 46.7), and progressively narrows from the base, which is 10.2 µm wide (7.8–15.3 µm; 
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFB009332FB4AFCE6" box="[1228,1242,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="9">n</emphasis>
= 6; 
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFAD99333FABEFCE7" box="[1301,1326,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="9">sd</emphasis>
= 2.6), to the distal opening, which is 2.8 µm wide (2.2–5 µm; 
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFCCA931EFC84FC3A" box="[774,788,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="9">n</emphasis>
= 8; 
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFC949310FCE2FC3A" box="[856,882,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="9">sd</emphasis>
= 0.9). The stylet wall is thickened in its distal portion, which is typical for this species (
<figureCitation id="6DFF2A5FFFF2AF6FFDA893FBFD4BFC1F" box="[612,731,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1242,1264]" captionTargetBox="[430,1155,193,1221]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[430,1156,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Macrostomum tuba Graff,1882.A, Dorsalview of a mature specimen;B, Posterior body region withdetails of the copulatory organs; C, Detail of the penis stylet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1084066/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figure 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F57B36DAFFF2AF6FFF0B93D8FC7FFBAA" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="9">
The female reproductive system is typical for the genus. The ovaries are located in the third part of body, arranged lateroventrally to the intestine (
<figureCitation id="6DFF2A5FFFF2AF6FFDA393A3FD7BFC57" box="[623,747,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1242,1264]" captionTargetBox="[430,1155,193,1221]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[430,1156,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Macrostomum tuba Graff,1882.A, Dorsalview of a mature specimen;B, Posterior body region withdetails of the copulatory organs; C, Detail of the penis stylet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1084066/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figure 5A</figureCitation>
). The female genital atrium is anterior to the false seminal vesicle. In some adult specimens, egg formation was observed in the atrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BDDE6551FFF2AF6FFF0B946BFA13FA8A" pageId="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F57B36DAFFF2AF6FFF0B946BFBB1FAB7" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFF0B946BFEABFB8F" bold="true" box="[199,315,1052,1077]" pageId="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
The most remarkable feature of 
<taxonomicName id="32C44D59FFF2AF6FFD6B946AFD6EFB8F" authorityName="Graff" authorityYear="1882" box="[679,766,1052,1077]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macrostomum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuba">
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFD6B946AFD6EFB8F" box="[679,766,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="9">M. tuba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the penis stylet, although the diameter of the base, size of shaft and diameter of the distal opening vary according to the region and habitat (
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFB8A9437FB4EFBE2" author="Hyman" box="[1094,1246,1087,1112]" pageId="9" refString="Hyman, L. H. (1936) Studies on the rhabdocoela of North America I. On Macrostomum tubum (Von Graff) 1882. Transactions of the American Microscopical Society, 55, 14 - 20." type="journal article" year="1936">Hyman 1936</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFB209437FA08FBE2" author="Ferguson" box="[1260,1432,1088,1112]" pageId="9" refString="Ferguson, F. F. (1939) A monograph of the genus Macrostomum O. Schmidt 1848. Part III. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 128, 4 - 68." type="journal article" year="1939">Ferguson 1939</bibRefCitation>
, 1940; 
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFF129413FEC2FBC7" author="Papi" box="[222,338,1124,1149]" pageId="9" refString="Papi, F. (1951) Ricerche sui Turbellaria Macrostomidae. Archivo Zoologico Italiano, 36, 289 - 342." type="journal article" year="1951">Papi 1951</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFE929412FE7BFBC7" author="Young" box="[350,491,1124,1149]" pageId="9" refString="Young, J. O. (1976) Systematic studies on limnic Macrostomum species (Turbellaria, Macrostomida) from east Africa. Zoologica Scripta, 5, 49 - 60. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1976. tb 00681. x" type="journal article" year="1976">Young 1976</bibRefCitation>
). The shape of the distal region of the stylet, with thickened walls, remains constant (
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFF5294FFFEF0FB1A" author="Wang" box="[158,352,1159,1184]" pageId="9" refString="Wang, A. - T., Hu, H. &amp; Luo, Z. G. (2004) The Biological characteristics of Macrostomum tuba in China. Chinese Journal of Zoology, 39 (4), 55 - 58" type="journal article" year="2004">
Wang 
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFF2B94FEFE89FB1A" box="[231,281,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation id="6DFF2A5FFFF2AF6FFEBA94F0FE7AFB1A" box="[374,490,1159,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1242,1264]" captionTargetBox="[430,1155,193,1221]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[430,1156,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Macrostomum tuba Graff,1882.A, Dorsalview of a mature specimen;B, Posterior body region withdetails of the copulatory organs; C, Detail of the penis stylet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1084066/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figure 5C</figureCitation>
), making easily the recognition of the species. Also, the stylet and body length in 
<taxonomicName id="32C44D59FFF2AF6FFAB194FEFF59FB7F" authorityName="Graff" authorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macrostomum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuba">
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFAB194FEFF59FB7F" italics="true" pageId="9">M. tuba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are variable; smaller body lengths usually have a straight and not slightly curved stylet, as observed in larger specimens (greater than 
<quantity id="323C9B3FFFF2AF6FFE6094A7FE7FFB52" box="[428,495,1232,1256]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFDCB94A7FD06FB52" author="Young" box="[519,662,1231,1256]" pageId="9" refString="Young, J. O. (1976) Systematic studies on limnic Macrostomum species (Turbellaria, Macrostomida) from east Africa. Zoologica Scripta, 5, 49 - 60. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1976. tb 00681. x" type="journal article" year="1976">Young 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFD6F94A6FCDEFB52" author="Ferguson" box="[675,846,1232,1257]" pageId="9" refString="Ferguson, F. F. (1939) A monograph of the genus Macrostomum O. Schmidt 1848. Part III. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 128, 4 - 68." type="journal article" year="1939">Ferguson 1939</bibRefCitation>
, 1940; 
<bibRefCitation id="91554B2BFFF2AF6FFC6E94A6FBA8FB52" author="Hyman" box="[930,1080,1231,1257]" pageId="9" refString="Hyman, L. H. (1936) Studies on the rhabdocoela of North America I. On Macrostomum tubum (Von Graff) 1882. Transactions of the American Microscopical Society, 55, 14 - 20." type="journal article" year="1936">Hyman 1936</bibRefCitation>
; Bois-Reymond Marcus 1957). These characteristics were observed in the specimens found in the Chillón River.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F57B36DAFFF2AF6FFF0B956EFA13FA8A" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1328]" box="[199,1411,1303,1328]" pageId="9">
<taxonomicName id="32C44D59FFF2AF6FFF0B956EFE8EFA8A" authorityName="Graff" authorityYear="1882" box="[199,286,1303,1328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macrostomum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuba">
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFF0B956EFE8EFA8A" box="[199,286,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="9">M. tuba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was associated with the same vegetation and physicochemical parameters as 
<taxonomicName id="32C44D59FFF2AF6FFB4E956EFA80FA8A" authorityName="Beklemischev" authorityYear="1951" box="[1154,1296,1305,1328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macrostomum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quiritium">
<emphasis id="C7B0EAC8FFF2AF6FFB4E956EFA80FA8A" box="[1154,1296,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="9">M. quiritium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="B8460361FFF2AF6FFAD29560FAE6FA8A" box="[1310,1398,1303,1328]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,239,872,895]" captionText="TABLE 2. Average values of the physicochemical parameters and characteristics of the sample sites in Humedales de Ventanilla (HV) and Chillón river (CR)." pageId="9">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
